Atlantic Richfield Co said it soldits Plan Cell Research Institute unit and its Arco Seed Cooperations in two transactions for undisclosed prices.    The company said it sold Dublin, Calif.-based Plant CellResearch to &lt;Montedision SpA> of Milan, Italy and ARCO Seed Coto U.F. Genetics of Hollister, Calif.    Atlantic Richfield said the divestitures are in line withits policy of focusing resources on oil, gas, chemical and coaloperations. Reuter&#3;